CGTN's "Media Challengers" team in Xi'an went to a shadow puppet studio in northwest China's Huazhou, around two hours drive from Xi'an, to learn shadow puppetry. They were assigned a mission to create an original shadow puppet play and perform a live show at Datang Everbright City. The team members brainstormed how to create the best performance, eventually deciding to combine elements of rap and Qinqiang Opera. Will they succeed in their mission to produce and perform their very own original puppet show? What did the combination of tradition and innovation bring to the show? Let's check it out!